The paper discusses the use of probabilistic programming frameworks for automated design of Bayesian signal processing algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on message passing in Forney-style factor graphs (FFGs) for inference. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and statistics (cs.ST) in the context of Bayesian inference, which are also possible sub-categories.
